task.summary: Default task

Solve GFG challenge, find the no of substrings with equal no of lowercase and uppercase letters using prefix sum.
Leveraged prior learning of converting the input into -1 or 1 when there are only two options in input.

Solve easy but tricky problem in GFG Challenge, find two coprime integers in a range of [L,R].
Trick was to return a pair of consecutive number as even/odd numbers are always coprime. Missed the edge case of 1,1 during the contest :(

Solve easy but extremely tricky to optimize, given a dictionary, find whether a string is present as a substring in another word using trie or rolling hash.
Trie implementation is very tricky and leverages reverse indexes similar to previously solved PrefixAndSuffixSearch. Was not able to think of trie solution.

Solve medium and a bit tricky problem, find the maximum monsters that can be killed by firing a gun every minute using greedy.
Was not able to solve this during the contest although the problem was simple :(

Solve medium and a bit tricky problem, find the maximum monsters that can be killed by firing a gun every minute using greedy.
Was not able to solve this during the contest although the problem was simple :(
Solve easy problem, reshape a given matrix of m*n size to provided r*c size using two pointers.
Solve medium problem, find the sum of each integer in a nested list multiplied by its "weight" using recursion.

Solve medium problem, find all simple fractions whose denominator <= n using GCD
Learnings: Calculation of GCD using euclidean algorithm.
Solve medium problem, find all the nodes in a tree whose value is greater than all the nodes lying in the path from root using recursion.
Update LargestNumberWithDigitsThatSumUpToTarget with another recursive top down solution that uses {index, targetSum} as DP states.
Solve tricky problem, find the number of pairs whose bitwise and is greater than bitwise xor by keeping track of highest one bit.
Solve GFG Coding challenge problem, find whether it's possible to equally distribute drinks among people using greedy.
Solve GFG coding challenge problem, find the ceil and floor of a key in a BST using recursion.
Solve medium problem, sort a string based on custom rank of each characters.

Solve medium and a bit tricky problem, find the array after incrementing the [start, end] with a value, multiple times using tricky prefix sum logic.
Happy to quickly solve this on my own. Initially was thinking towards a segment tree solution but then realized it's just a medium problem :)

Solve medium and a bit tricky problem, find the array after incrementing the [start, end] with a value, multiple times using tricky prefix sum logic.
Happy to quickly solve this on my own. Initially was thinking towards a segment tree solution but then realized it's just a medium problem :)

Solve medium and a bit tricky problem, find the array after incrementing the [start, end] with a value, multiple times using tricky prefix sum logic.
Happy to quickly solve this on my own. Initially was thinking towards a segment tree solution but then realized it's just a medium problem :)

Solve medium and extremely tricky to optimize, find no of triplets that forms valid triangles using two pointers.
Two pointers solution was extremely tricky to visualize but the binary search solution was relatively easy.
Solve easy problem, find the number of triplets which satisfies a^2 + b^2 = c^2 and a,b,c <= n using brute force.
Solve medium problem, find the nearest exit from an entrance in maze using BFS.

Solve hard and a bit tricky problem, find the minimum cost to reach a target node in a specified amount of time using modified Djikstra
Leveraged prior learnings from solving CheapestFlightWithinKStop

Solve easy and a bit tricky to optimize, find whether a string can generated by repeating some of the characters using two pointers.
I was able to solve it using O(n) extra space, tricky thing was to solve it in O(1) space.

Solve medium and extremely tricky to optimize, find the smallest no of subsequences of a string that can be concatenated to form a target string using binary search, brute force and DP
Learnings: DP solution was very interesting and new to me. It allowed to perform query in O(1) time and reduced the time complexity to linear. Very cool.
Solve medium problem, prune a binary tree of subtrees not containing 1 using recursion.
Solve medium and a bit tricky problem

Solve hard and a bit tricky problem, find all the shortest paths that can transform a word into another word using BFS and pruning.
Learnings: Pruning was critical to avoid TLE.

Solve hard and a bit tricky problem, find all the shortest paths that can transform a word into another word using BFS and pruning.
Learnings: Pruning was critical to avoid TLE.

Solve hard problem, reverse linked list in groups of size k using 3 pointers.
Leveraged prior learnings of reversing an entire linked list using 3 pointers.
Update priority queue solution for classical problem MeetingsRoom2

Solve medium and a bit tricky range interval problem, find the number of the smallest unoccupied chair given the arrival and leave time for all the person using greedy.
Levered prior learnings of solving range interval problems.
Add Lakoten interview experience for Equities trading developer.
Add another solution to find LCA of two nodes in a n-ary tree in SmallestCommonRegion using recursion.
Simplify optimized solution in ValidTriangleNumber using the same logic as ThreeSumSmaller

Solve medium assignment problem, find the optimal assignment pattern such that each student gets one mentor and each mentor gets one student using backtracking and bitmasking.
Also update CampusBikes with the possibility of greedy being a wrong approach to solve the problem.
Learnings: Initially tried solving the problem using greedy during contest, got WA, switched to backtracking.

Solve medium problem, find the largest number that can be generating after mutating a substring using greedy.
Learnings: Leveraged prior learning of solving similar string mutation problem LargestOddNumberInString
Solve medium and a bit tricky problem, given various intervals and a color, find the final sum of the colors at each index using prefix sum.

Solve medium problem, find the total sum of all the keys that starts with a prefix using Trie.
Leveraged prior learning of storing useful information directly in trie node.
Add hint to understand Euclidean algorithm to find GCD
Add DP State optimization solution for FormLargestNumberWithDigitsThatSumUpToTarget
Fix typo and simplify code in PredictTheWinner
Add comment on why greedy approach works in CampusBikes
Solve medium problem, perform level order traversal on a n-ary tree using BFS
Solve easy problem, count no of negative numbers in a row and column sorted matrix using two pointers.

Solve medium and a bit tricky to understand problem, find whether a move is legal or not by iterating in 8 directions.
Was unable to solve this question in the contest as I wrongly assumed that the endpoint must end on the border :(
Solve easy problem, find whether a prefix of given arrays of words can result in a target string using two pointers.

Solve medium problem and a bit tricky to optimize runtime, remove maximum stones to minimize the total using greedy / priority queue or bucket/counting sort.
Learnings: Counting sort can be used to optimize runtime when we are interested only in min/max.

Solve medium and a bit tricky problem, reorder an array such that every adjacent pair of elements equals [x, 2*x] using greedy.
Learnings: Reading the problem statement carefully is very important. Lately I have been misreading them quite a lot, which is costing me a lot :(
Solve medium and a bit tricky problem, find the min cost to flip a string to monotone increasing using two pass solution.
Solve medium and a bit tricky maths problem, find the min steps required to find the first floor at which an egg breaks given 2 eggs and N floors using maths or DP
